qas.question: What is the ancient name of Kathmandu?
How does कान्तिपुर transliterate into English?
How do you say place in Sanskrit?
What is the English translation of Mahanagar?

context: The colophons of ancient manuscripts, dated as late as the 20th century, refer to Kathmandu as <a0_0>Kasthamandap Mahanagar<a0_0/> in Nepal Mandala. Mahanagar means "<a4_0>great city<a4_0/>". The city is called "Kasthamandap" in a vow that Buddhist priests still recite to this day. Thus, Kathmandu is also known as Kasthamandap. During medieval times, the city was sometimes called <a1_0>Kantipur<a1_0/> (कान्तिपुर). This name is derived from two Sanskrit words - Kanti and pur. "Kanti" is one of the names of the Goddess <a2_0>Lakshmi<a2_0/>, and "<a3_0>pur<a3_0/>" means place.
